      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(infra): prefix channelId with channel: when migrating to target",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `normalizeMessageActionInput` migrates `channelId` → `target` for `\"to\"`-mode actions (e.g. `read`, `send`), bare numeric Discord snowflakes lose the `preferredKind: \"group\"` context that `resolveActionTarget` applied when processing `channelId` directly. The Discord target parser then throws `\"Ambiguous Discord recipient\"` because it cannot tell if a bare numeric is a user or channel ID.\n\nPrefix bare `channelId` values with `channel:` during migration, since the field semantically means \"this is a channel\". Only apply the prefix for `\"to\"`-mode actions where `channelId` is a legacy fallback — not for `\"channelId\"`-mode actions (e.g. `channel-info`) where `channelId` is the primary target field.\n\n## Root cause\n\n1. Model calls `message(action=\"read\", channelId=\"1507887702379335791\")` — a bare Discord snowflake\n2. `normalizeMessageActionInput` migrates `channelId` → `target` (since `read` is a `\"to\"`-mode action) but copies the bare value without prefix\n3. `resolveActionTarget` processes the migrated `target`/`to` without `preferredKind` (which was only applied to the `channelId` path)\n4. Discord target parser receives a bare numeric without `defaultKind`, throws `\"Ambiguous Discord recipient\"`\n\nBefore this fix, `resolveActionTarget` had two code paths:\n- `to` path: no `preferredKind` → bare numerics ambiguous\n- `channelId` path: `preferredKind: \"group\"` → bare numerics resolved as channels\n\nThe migration collapsed both paths into the `to` path, losing the `preferredKind` context.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior**: `message(action=\"read\")` with bare numeric `channelId` throws `\"Ambiguous Discord recipient\"` on Discord\n\n**Environment**: OpenClaw v2026.5.30-beta.1, Discord channel `1507887702379335791`\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Music generation completion agent calls `message(action=\"read\", channelId=\"1507887702379335791\", limit=50)` to fetch channel context\n2. `normalizeMessageActionInput` migrates `channelId` → `target` as bare `\"1507887702379335791\"` (no `channel:` prefix)\n3. `resolveActionTarget` processes `to=\"1507887702379335791\"` without `preferredKind`\n4. Discord target parser cannot disambiguate bare numeric, throws\n\n**Evidence**:\n```\n[tools] message failed: Ambiguous Discord recipient \"1507887702379335791\". For DMs use \"user:1507887702379335791\" or \"<@1507887702379335791>\"; for channels use \"channel:1507887702379335791\". raw_params={\"action\":\"read\",\"channel\":\"discord\",\"channelId\":\"1507887702379335791\",\"limit\":50}\n```\n(8 occurrences at 2026-05-31T08:08–08:18 UTC, post media-reply-instruction fix)\n\n**Observed result**: After fix, `channelId: \"1507887702379335791\"` is migrated to `target: \"channel:1507887702379335791\"`, which the Discord target parser resolves unambiguously as a channel.\n\n**Not tested**: Live deployment of this specific fix (tested via source-level reasoning and unit tests). Related `action=\"send\"` ambiguous-recipient bug was confirmed fixed via Dicky dist patch (PR #88542).\n",
        "branch": "codex/fix-channelid-ambiguous-recipient",
